<item>
            <title>[LU-19495] suboptimal object placement in lfs mirror extend</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19495</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I just noticed that sometimes lfs mirror extend -N creates new objects on used OSTs:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
# lfs setstripe -c2 $tf
# lfs mirror extend -N $tf
# lfs getstripe -v $tf | grep l_ost_idx
      -   0: { l_ost_idx:   0, l_fid: [0x240000400:0x2:0x0] }
      -   1: { l_ost_idx:   1, l_fid: [0x280000400:0x2:0x0] }
      -   0: { l_ost_idx:   3, l_fid: [0x300000400:0x3:0x0] }
      -   1: { l_ost_idx:   0, l_fid: [0x240000400:0x3:0x0] }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;all OSTs are fresh, just formatted&lt;/p&gt;</description>
